    <!-- 01 Hook -->
    <div class="slide">
        <span class="slide-num">01 / 11</span>
        <div class="slide-label">Parachute &mdash; Open Parachute, PBC</div>
        <h1>Your AI doesn't know you.</h1>
        <p>Every conversation starts fresh. Your real thinking is scattered across a dozen apps. The tool that could actually help you think better has never heard of you.</p>
        <p>We're building the extended mind that changes that.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- 02 Problem -->
    <div class="slide">
        <span class="slide-num">02 / 11</span>
        <div class="slide-label">The Problem</div>
        <h2>Powerful AI. No memory. No trust.</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Scattered thinking</strong> &mdash; voice memos here, typed notes there, AI conversations that vanish</li>
            <li><strong>No continuity</strong> &mdash; every AI session starts cold; you re-explain your context every time</li>
            <li><strong>No trust</strong> &mdash; the only way to get real help is to share your real thinking, but you wouldn't trust most tools with that</li>
            <li><strong>Wrong layer</strong> &mdash; existing tools ask you to learn the system; the system should learn you</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- 03 Why Now -->
    <div class="slide">
        <span class="slide-num">03 / 11</span>
        <div class="slide-label">Why Now</div>
        <h2>Three things converged.</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Models crossed a threshold</strong> &mdash; Claude and similar models are genuinely useful for personal thinking, not just coding tasks</li>
            <li><strong>Local-first is viable</strong> &mdash; on-device voice transcription (Parakeet / Sherpa-ONNX) works offline, at quality</li>
            <li><strong>Privacy is a real concern</strong> &mdash; people are increasingly aware of where their data goes; open source + local-first is the only honest answer</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">The personal AI computer category is forming. The question is who builds it in a way people can actually trust.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- 04 Solution -->
    <div class="slide">
        <span class="slide-num">04 / 11</span>
        <div class="slide-label">The Solution</div>
        <h2>Two products. One extended mind.</h2>
        <div class="two-col">
            <div class="col-card">
                <h3>Parachute Daily</h3>
                <p>Journaling with gentle AI. For everyone.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Voice or text capture, wherever you think</li>
                    <li>Daily AI reflections, weekly synthesis</li>
                    <li>Pattern detection over time</li>
                    <li>Hosted, subscription, no setup</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="col-card">
                <h3>Parachute Computer</h3>
                <p>Full agentic platform. For power users.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Brain knowledge graph + Chat + Daily</li>
                    <li>Three trust tiers, Docker sandbox</li>
                    <li>Telegram, Discord, Matrix bots</li>
                    <li>Open source, self-hosted or managed</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- 05 Flywheel -->
    <div class="slide">
        <span class="slide-num">05 / 11</span>
